name: Médecins Sans Frontières International
goal: Médecins Sans Frontières (MSF) is an international, independent, medical humanitarian organisation that delivers emergency aid to people affected by armed conflict, epidemics, natural disasters and exclusion from healthcare. MSF offers assistance to people based on need, irrespective of race, religion, gender or political affiliation.
interests: Customs, Humanitarian aid and civil protection, Institutional affairs, International co-operation and development, Public Health, Research and innovation, Trade
euInitiatives: Horizon 2020, Research Framework Programme, IP incentives debates, Trade agreements, Reform Asylum System, Humanitarian files,
